  summary: "Science and technology policy refers to the set of government actions, laws, and funding decisions aimed at promoting scientific research and technological innovation, as well as addressing their societal impacts. It covers areas like research funding, intellectual property rights, and ethical guidelines. For AI policy, this involves government strategies for investing in AI research, setting standards for AI development, regulating AI\'s use in various sectors, and managing its economic and social consequences.",
